3 B(1). In order to be eligible to provide mobile crisis response services, a
4 provider shall be licensed in accordance with R.S. 40:2152 et seq. and shall
5 coordinate and share information with the Louisiana Department of Health
6 sanctioned Crisis Hub.
7 (2). In order to be eligible to provide behavioral health crisis care services,
8 a provider shall be licensed in accordance with R.S. 40:2152 et seq. or R.S.
9 40:2180.11 et seq. and shall coordinate and share information with the Louisiana
10 Department of Health sanctioned Crisis Hub.
11 C. For the purposes of this Section, the following terms have the meanings
12 ascribed to them:
13 (1) “Behavioral Health Crisis Care” means an initial or emergency crisis
14 response intended to provide relief, resolution and intervention through crisis
15 supports and services during the first phase of a crisis in the community for adults.
16 (a) Services are recovery-oriented and time-limited for up to twenty-three
17 hours per intervention, generally addressing a single episode that enables an
18 individual to return home with community-based services for support or be
19 transitioned to a higher level of care as appropriate if the crisis is unable to be
20 resolved.
21 (b) Eligible providers operate twenty-four hours per day, seven days a week
22 as a walk-in center providing short-term mental health crisis response, offering a
23 community-based voluntary home-like alternative to more restrictive settings.
24 (c) Eligible providers must be licensed in accordance with R.S. 40:1252 et
25 seq. or R.S. 40:2180.11 et seq. and must coordinate and share information with the
26 Louisiana Department of Health sanctioned Crisis Hub.
27 (2) “Health insurance issuer” means any entity that offers health insurance
28 coverage through a policy or certificate of insurance subject to state law that
29 regulates the business of insurance.
